1.00	Belgium_in_the_Eurovision_Song_Contest_1977	Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 1977	Belgium was represented by Dream Express, with the song '"A Million in One, Two, Three", at the 1977 Eurovision Song Contest, which took place in London on 7 May. The selection consisted of three semi-finals, followed by the final on 5 February. All the shows were hosted by Luc Appermont and took place at the Amerikaans Theater in Brussels.	
